2008). Investment in high speed rail does not always result in such reduction. High speed
lines between Stockholm and Gothenburg (460 km) and Stockholm and Malmoe (615 km),
Sweden's three largest cities, are expected to cut travel times by respectively 27 and 44 per
cent (from 2:45 to 2:00 hours in the case of Stockholm-Gothenburg). An investigation on
behalf of the Swedish government (UOH, 2009) nevertheless thinks that the investment (a
combination of the two new lines) would result in:
7.7 billion more pkm by rail;
1.6 billion pkm less by aviation;
3.1 billion pkm less by car;
0.1 billion pkm less by bus.
